Good morning everyone,
After having had a family meeting, and some discussions we have decided
that Lukasi will be staying in Kuujjuaq in June to attend his  secondary 5
graduation along with his classmates.  We came to this  decision as a
family and are sorry if we have inconvenienced anyone.

We strongly believe Lukasi should prioritize his education for his future
and that is one of the many reasons why we feel this is the right decision
for our son.

We hope a replacement can be found at this late hour for this wonderful
opportunity to participate in this nation wide trip.  We would like to
thank everyone involved for their time and for giving our son
opportunities that he has many positive memories about.


Yours sincerely,

Louisa Whiteley Tukkiapik
Concerned parent

